Liz Truss light-heartedly asked Alastair Stewart if she could bring the discussion to an end when he made a reference to an infamous Theresa May interview where the former Prime Minister revealed the “naughtiest thing” she’d ever done was “run through fields of wheat”. The GB News presenter went on to tease Truss about her relationship with Downing Street cat Larry. Stewart asked: “I promised you and your people faithfully I wouldn’t be asking you about the naughtiest thing you done, running through hayfields or anything like that…” Truss joked: “Well I’m pleased to hear that can we terminate this interview now?” “That would make great telly,” Stewart quipped. More to follow…